{
  "number": 411,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/411",
  "title": "Documentation: bottom left links are redundant/taking too much space?",
  "body": "![2015-11-02-184805_335x670_scrot](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/123822/10889432/4ca10436-8192-11e5-954a-531ce8de2c18.png)\n\nI am talking about the octocat/fork/stackoverflow icons.\n\nRight now they are sticky to the documentation and are taking a good visual spot/place. But as a developer I would only need to see the octocat in the top right of the top menu.\n\nAlso the fork and octocat are redirecting to the same thing, and even \"fixing\" the fork button to actually fork the project would be weird.\n\nYou never really want to fork from a website that is not github, you just want to see the github project and browse it first.\n\nI would put the octocat in top right and allow this space to be used for the left menu. Also the left menu will at some point take more height space so it will start looking weird as a fixed position menu.\n\nWhat do you think?\n",
